the only way I have found to reliably get the (-at-)&#*(-at-) things out is to
break em up with a punch and hammer....not fun, WEAR GOGGLES, maybe 50/50
odds of damaging the hole too.  make sure all of the pieces are out before
trying to drill it over as the least little piece will booger the new
drill

